WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:27.832 align:middle line:90%


00:00:27.832 --> 00:00:29.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: If
you've been reading

00:00:29.540 --> 00:00:32.000 align:middle line:84%
metaphysical and science
books to gather knowledge

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.530 align:middle line:84%
for decades as I have,
there are times when I just

00:00:34.530 --> 00:00:36.810 align:middle line:84%
want to have it handed
to me unvarnished,

00:00:36.810 --> 00:00:39.380 align:middle line:84%
no references, no
politically-correct language,

00:00:39.380 --> 00:00:40.850 align:middle line:90%
just tell me what you know.

00:00:40.850 --> 00:00:42.730 align:middle line:84%
Not surprisingly,
some of the authors

00:00:42.730 --> 00:00:44.510 align:middle line:84%
of these heavyweight
books themselves

00:00:44.510 --> 00:00:48.220 align:middle line:84%
want wider expression such a
scientist and shaman Barbara

00:00:48.220 --> 00:00:49.160 align:middle line:90%
Hand Clow.

00:00:49.160 --> 00:00:50.940 align:middle line:84%
Toward that end,
she and others have

00:00:50.940 --> 00:00:54.060 align:middle line:84%
turned to fiction, which adds
fun and excitement to the read

00:00:54.060 --> 00:00:57.510 align:middle line:84%
while getting to the deep
and controversial information

00:00:57.510 --> 00:01:00.360 align:middle line:84%
quickly, and there is a lot
of controversial information

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:01.560 align:middle line:90%
in "The Ruby Crystal."

00:01:01.560 --> 00:01:04.470 align:middle line:84%
And first of all, I want
to say I feel so honored.

00:01:04.470 --> 00:01:07.870 align:middle line:84%
This is your very first public
discussion about this book.

00:01:07.870 --> 00:01:09.182 align:middle line:90%
The ink is barely dry.

00:01:09.182 --> 00:01:09.890 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yes.

00:01:09.890 --> 00:01:10.590 align:middle line:90%
That's true, Regina.

00:01:10.590 --> 00:01:13.215 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know how it's going
to go for me because I've never

00:01:13.215 --> 00:01:15.370 align:middle line:84%
talked about it before,
but we'll give it a try.

00:01:15.370 --> 00:01:17.859 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, And
these are subjects

00:01:17.859 --> 00:01:19.400 align:middle line:84%
that are near and
dear to your heart,

00:01:19.400 --> 00:01:23.620 align:middle line:84%
and we talked a little bit about
it at the end a conversation

00:01:23.620 --> 00:01:26.220 align:middle line:84%
a while back about
why turn to fiction,

00:01:26.220 --> 00:01:28.100 align:middle line:90%
And there's a reason for that.

00:01:28.100 --> 00:01:30.017 align:middle line:84%
So give us your reason
for turning to fiction.

00:01:30.017 --> 00:01:32.683 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: Well, in my case, I
always wanted to write fiction.

00:01:32.683 --> 00:01:33.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:01:33.280 --> 00:01:34.988 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: But when
I started my career

00:01:34.988 --> 00:01:37.570 align:middle line:84%
as a writer 35 years ago,
all I could have done

00:01:37.570 --> 00:01:40.225 align:middle line:84%
was write novels about
violence, crime, and lust,

00:01:40.225 --> 00:01:43.370 align:middle line:84%
and hideous subjects as
far as I'm concerned.

00:01:43.370 --> 00:01:47.700 align:middle line:84%
And so I went into nonfiction
and became successful.

00:01:47.700 --> 00:01:50.320 align:middle line:84%
And then when I finally
became successful enough,

00:01:50.320 --> 00:01:53.140 align:middle line:84%
I decided it's time to
do what I want to do.

00:01:53.140 --> 00:01:55.220 align:middle line:84%
And so I turned back
to writing fiction.

00:01:55.220 --> 00:01:56.970 align:middle line:90%
I opened up that gate.

00:01:56.970 --> 00:01:59.770 align:middle line:84%
And the way it worked was
just utterly fascinating.

00:01:59.770 --> 00:02:02.600 align:middle line:84%
Once I made an
agreement with myself

00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:05.190 align:middle line:84%
that I could write fiction
and I would write fiction,

00:02:05.190 --> 00:02:07.990 align:middle line:84%
then what happened is,
one day two years ago,

00:02:07.990 --> 00:02:12.680 align:middle line:84%
May of 2011, all of the
characters except for one just

00:02:12.680 --> 00:02:14.100 align:middle line:90%
showed up one day.

00:02:14.100 --> 00:02:16.610 align:middle line:84%
And I took out a yellow
tablet and I wrote down

00:02:16.610 --> 00:02:20.160 align:middle line:84%
their names, their ages,
and their backgrounds,

00:02:20.160 --> 00:02:23.030 align:middle line:84%
and where they lived, and
they all became a group,

00:02:23.030 --> 00:02:24.670 align:middle line:90%
and they all created the novel.

00:02:24.670 --> 00:02:26.220 align:middle line:90%
I never plotted it.

00:02:26.220 --> 00:02:29.410 align:middle line:84%
I simply sat down every
day from 9:00 to 12:00

00:02:29.410 --> 00:02:32.850 align:middle line:84%
and got my characters together,
and they wrote the novel.

00:02:32.850 --> 00:02:34.610 align:middle line:84%
And now that I'm
finished with it,

00:02:34.610 --> 00:02:36.697 align:middle line:84%
I realized that they're
all fragments of myself.

00:02:36.697 --> 00:02:37.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:02:37.280 --> 00:02:37.710 align:middle line:90%
Of course.

00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:39.800 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: And I realized
that what was really going on

00:02:39.800 --> 00:02:41.930 align:middle line:84%
with me-- I'm still
working on the same issues.

00:02:41.930 --> 00:02:44.050 align:middle line:84%
I'm still working on
multi-dimensionality.

00:02:44.050 --> 00:02:47.049 align:middle line:84%
I'm still working on the
fourth dimensional control

00:02:47.049 --> 00:02:47.590 align:middle line:90%
of the world.

00:02:47.590 --> 00:02:49.610 align:middle line:84%
I'm still working
on the same stuff.

00:02:49.610 --> 00:02:51.470 align:middle line:84%
But I realized that
I wanted to have

00:02:51.470 --> 00:02:53.090 align:middle line:84%
a whole bunch of
characters who had

00:02:53.090 --> 00:02:54.580 align:middle line:90%
different kinds of backgrounds.

00:02:54.580 --> 00:02:58.552 align:middle line:84%
Like one guy is a really
good-looking, Jewish guy

00:02:58.552 --> 00:03:00.760 align:middle line:84%
from New York who's working
for "The New York Times,"

00:03:00.760 --> 00:03:04.480 align:middle line:84%
and he's in the Vatican
doing a reporter patrol

00:03:04.480 --> 00:03:06.190 align:middle line:90%
on priestly sexual abuse.

00:03:06.190 --> 00:03:09.130 align:middle line:84%
Another character is a
very attractive young woman

00:03:09.130 --> 00:03:12.040 align:middle line:84%
who's getting her PhD
in patristics, which

00:03:12.040 --> 00:03:14.640 align:middle line:84%
is study of the
early church fathers.

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:16.680 align:middle line:84%
She's in Rome on
assignment, and they

00:03:16.680 --> 00:03:18.580 align:middle line:84%
run into each
other accidentally.

00:03:18.580 --> 00:03:20.954 align:middle line:84%
And that was the best part
of it was the way they met

00:03:20.954 --> 00:03:22.620 align:middle line:84%
and the way they got
to know each other.

00:03:22.620 --> 00:03:22.800 align:middle line:90%
It was so much fun.

00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:22.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:23.830 align:middle line:90%
And I know that place.

00:03:23.830 --> 00:03:24.830 align:middle line:90%
I've been there in Rome.

00:03:24.830 --> 00:03:28.110 align:middle line:84%
It's nice because you're
using some familiar areas

00:03:28.110 --> 00:03:30.960 align:middle line:84%
and landmarks within Rome
that many of us have seen

00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:32.970 align:middle line:84%
and you kind of anchor
us into your story too.

00:03:32.970 --> 00:03:33.280 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: That's right.

00:03:33.280 --> 00:03:36.100 align:middle line:84%
And I had a lot of fun doing
that, because I love Italy.

00:03:36.100 --> 00:03:39.090 align:middle line:84%
I particularly love
Tuscany, and I love Rome.

00:03:39.090 --> 00:03:41.490 align:middle line:84%
And so then what I had
to do with that was,

00:03:41.490 --> 00:03:43.030 align:middle line:84%
I didn't necessarily
have everything

00:03:43.030 --> 00:03:45.420 align:middle line:84%
I needed so most of the
locations in the novel

00:03:45.420 --> 00:03:47.970 align:middle line:84%
are actual places
such as the Vatican

00:03:47.970 --> 00:03:51.110 align:middle line:84%
or such as various places
in Tuscany and Siena,

00:03:51.110 --> 00:03:53.320 align:middle line:84%
but many other
places are fictional.

00:03:53.320 --> 00:03:55.750 align:middle line:84%
So for example,
this young reporter

00:03:55.750 --> 00:03:59.480 align:middle line:84%
runs into the young
woman near a site, which

00:03:59.480 --> 00:04:02.240 align:middle line:84%
was once-- it's an
archaeological site, which

00:04:02.240 --> 00:04:03.610 align:middle line:90%
was the House of Cumuli.

00:04:03.610 --> 00:04:05.450 align:middle line:90%
That's all fictional.

00:04:05.450 --> 00:04:06.466 align:middle line:90%
But if you go to Rome--

00:04:06.466 --> 00:04:08.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But archaeological
site with all the cats

00:04:08.590 --> 00:04:09.360 align:middle line:90%
is not fictional.

00:04:09.360 --> 00:04:09.745 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: No.

00:04:09.745 --> 00:04:10.360 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:04:10.360 --> 00:04:11.280 align:middle line:90%
No, it actually is.

00:04:11.280 --> 00:04:12.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, but
it exists in real life.

00:04:12.970 --> 00:04:13.290 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: No.

00:04:13.290 --> 00:04:13.915 align:middle line:90%
No, it doesn't.

00:04:13.915 --> 00:04:14.810 align:middle line:90%
It's fictional.

00:04:14.810 --> 00:04:15.518 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Really?

00:04:15.518 --> 00:04:18.045 align:middle line:84%
What about that site with
all those wild, stray cats?

00:04:18.045 --> 00:04:18.160 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: No.

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:19.743 align:middle line:84%
First of all, what
you're thinking of,

00:04:19.743 --> 00:04:22.330 align:middle line:84%
and it's where it came from is
that when you go around Rome,

00:04:22.330 --> 00:04:24.312 align:middle line:84%
you see these walls
and you see these digs.

00:04:24.312 --> 00:04:26.270 align:middle line:84%
And if you look down in
them, there's a plaque,

00:04:26.270 --> 00:04:27.486 align:middle line:90%
and it tells you what it is.

00:04:27.486 --> 00:04:29.360 align:middle line:84%
And then there's cats
running around usually.

00:04:29.360 --> 00:04:29.705 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:04:29.705 --> 00:04:31.980 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: But in this
case, as far as I know,

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:34.930 align:middle line:84%
there is no archeol-- Now,
I'm going to Italy in May

00:04:34.930 --> 00:04:36.680 align:middle line:84%
to fact check, because
I haven't been back

00:04:36.680 --> 00:04:37.860 align:middle line:90%
in about 10 or 15 years.

00:04:37.860 --> 00:04:38.460 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, good.

00:04:38.460 --> 00:04:38.560 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:04:38.560 --> 00:04:38.660 align:middle line:90%
Cool.

00:04:38.660 --> 00:04:40.720 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: And maybe there
is a site for the House of--

00:04:40.720 --> 00:04:40.935 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, no.

00:04:40.935 --> 00:04:42.410 align:middle line:84%
I was probably just jumbling
what you were speaking about.

00:04:42.410 --> 00:04:42.760 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: No.

00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:42.880 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:04:42.880 --> 00:04:44.630 align:middle line:84%
But maybe I made it so real
that you thought it was real.

00:04:44.630 --> 00:04:46.430 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have an
afterward in the book,

00:04:46.430 --> 00:04:48.080 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to
delineate what's fictional

00:04:48.080 --> 00:04:49.790 align:middle line:84%
and what's not fictional,
because I think

00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:52.700 align:middle line:84%
that, for instance, I
also was able to write

00:04:52.700 --> 00:04:56.160 align:middle line:84%
this book because I was lucky
enough to know an aristocratic

00:04:56.160 --> 00:04:58.720 align:middle line:84%
family in Tuscany and
visit their castle

00:04:58.720 --> 00:04:59.720 align:middle line:90%
and visit their home.

00:04:59.720 --> 00:05:01.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I wondered about
that when I was reading it.

00:05:01.970 --> 00:05:04.330 align:middle line:84%
It seemed as though that
was an actual experience

00:05:04.330 --> 00:05:05.620 align:middle line:90%
that you were basing it on.

00:05:05.620 --> 00:05:06.370 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:08.040 align:middle line:84%
So I had a wonderful,
deep experience

00:05:08.040 --> 00:05:09.470 align:middle line:84%
that went over a
number of years.

00:05:09.470 --> 00:05:09.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: How rich.

00:05:09.790 --> 00:05:11.680 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: But I'm not
giving the correct name

00:05:11.680 --> 00:05:13.005 align:middle line:84%
of their castle
and their family--

00:05:13.005 --> 00:05:13.076 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:05:13.076 --> 00:05:13.585 align:middle line:90%
Of course not.

00:05:13.585 --> 00:05:15.500 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: --just because I
just think it would be better.

00:05:15.500 --> 00:05:16.550 align:middle line:90%
It's not necessary.

00:05:16.550 --> 00:05:19.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then you have
the gorgeous, handsome artist,

00:05:19.350 --> 00:05:21.750 align:middle line:84%
Armando, that, of
course, at first blush,

00:05:21.750 --> 00:05:23.480 align:middle line:90%
all women fall in love with.

00:05:23.480 --> 00:05:24.940 align:middle line:90%
We can't help ourselves.

00:05:24.940 --> 00:05:25.690 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:05:25.690 --> 00:05:27.707 align:middle line:90%
Armando Carolioni, right?

00:05:27.707 --> 00:05:28.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:05:28.290 --> 00:05:28.789 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:05:28.789 --> 00:05:29.640 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:05:29.640 --> 00:05:30.820 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:05:30.820 --> 00:05:33.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But the
subject itself is really

00:05:33.240 --> 00:05:35.490 align:middle line:84%
something that has disturbed
you for a long time

00:05:35.490 --> 00:05:36.940 align:middle line:84%
and intrigued you
for a long time.

00:05:36.940 --> 00:05:37.225 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yes.

00:05:37.225 --> 00:05:38.974 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it's
something that I really

00:05:38.974 --> 00:05:41.170 align:middle line:84%
think needs to be
gotten out on the table.

00:05:41.170 --> 00:05:43.630 align:middle line:84%
And before we get
into it, I want

00:05:43.630 --> 00:05:46.450 align:middle line:84%
to say what I appreciated
about this, even though it's

00:05:46.450 --> 00:05:51.400 align:middle line:84%
a beautiful, fun, sexy
story that's carrying it,

00:05:51.400 --> 00:05:54.510 align:middle line:84%
when you get into this, you're
talking multi-dimensionality.

00:05:54.510 --> 00:05:57.690 align:middle line:84%
You're talking about
a condition that

00:05:57.690 --> 00:06:00.700 align:middle line:84%
has been perpetrated by the
Roman Catholic Church that

00:06:00.700 --> 00:06:04.070 align:middle line:84%
is just devastating to our
psyche that is actually being

00:06:04.070 --> 00:06:06.015 align:middle line:84%
driven from other
dimensional forces.

00:06:06.015 --> 00:06:06.380 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: That's right.

00:06:06.380 --> 00:06:08.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that's
the part you don't ever

00:06:08.370 --> 00:06:09.340 align:middle line:90%
hear come into the question.

00:06:09.340 --> 00:06:11.550 align:middle line:84%
It's certainly not going to make
"The New York Times." right?

00:06:11.550 --> 00:06:12.225 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: That's right.

00:06:12.225 --> 00:06:13.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And it's important.

00:06:13.500 --> 00:06:16.855 align:middle line:84%
So tell us a little bit--
before we get deeply into it.

00:06:16.855 --> 00:06:18.480 align:middle line:84%
Right at the very
beginning of the book

00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:20.520 align:middle line:84%
you talk about the
Church of Marcion

00:06:20.520 --> 00:06:22.330 align:middle line:90%
and this figure, Marcion.

00:06:22.330 --> 00:06:24.810 align:middle line:84%
I found that really intriguing
because I knew nothing

00:06:24.810 --> 00:06:27.530 align:middle line:84%
about this figure in
religious history.

00:06:27.530 --> 00:06:30.400 align:middle line:84%
So take some time
to explain to us who

00:06:30.400 --> 00:06:33.020 align:middle line:84%
this was, when they
were, what they attempted

00:06:33.020 --> 00:06:37.615 align:middle line:84%
to do to uplift and preserve
Christianity and why.

00:06:37.615 --> 00:06:40.080 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: So this
is Marcion of Pontus,

00:06:40.080 --> 00:06:45.890 align:middle line:84%
and he was alive in the east
like in the region of Turkey,

00:06:45.890 --> 00:06:47.390 align:middle line:90%
basic region of the Middle East.

00:06:47.390 --> 00:06:51.680 align:middle line:84%
And he was on the planet
from about 70 AD probably

00:06:51.680 --> 00:06:53.950 align:middle line:90%
to about 150 AD.

00:06:53.950 --> 00:06:55.900 align:middle line:84%
What we know about
him historically

00:06:55.900 --> 00:06:59.330 align:middle line:84%
was that he was
excommunicated in 144 AD.

00:06:59.330 --> 00:07:01.900 align:middle line:90%
We do have one exact date.

00:07:01.900 --> 00:07:05.150 align:middle line:84%
But what we do know about him
besides his excommunication

00:07:05.150 --> 00:07:08.670 align:middle line:84%
by the Roman church
is that he was

00:07:08.670 --> 00:07:11.070 align:middle line:84%
a bishop, an early
Christian bishop.

00:07:11.070 --> 00:07:13.150 align:middle line:84%
And of course, most
people who were Christians

00:07:13.150 --> 00:07:15.180 align:middle line:84%
were Jewish converts,
so of course, he

00:07:15.180 --> 00:07:16.730 align:middle line:90%
has a Jewish background.

00:07:16.730 --> 00:07:20.340 align:middle line:84%
And then his father was also
an early Christian bishop.

00:07:20.340 --> 00:07:21.860 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is
extremely interesting

00:07:21.860 --> 00:07:23.276 align:middle line:84%
because his father
would have been

00:07:23.276 --> 00:07:25.390 align:middle line:90%
the same age as Paul of Tarsus.

00:07:25.390 --> 00:07:28.200 align:middle line:84%
And so Paul had a very
big influence on Marcion,

00:07:28.200 --> 00:07:30.950 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not going to get into
New Testament and biblical

00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:32.840 align:middle line:84%
things and I didn't
in the book either

00:07:32.840 --> 00:07:34.230 align:middle line:90%
because it's pretty boring.

00:07:34.230 --> 00:07:36.400 align:middle line:84%
But what's important
about Marcion is,

00:07:36.400 --> 00:07:38.320 align:middle line:84%
he was an early
Christian bishop.

00:07:38.320 --> 00:07:42.800 align:middle line:84%
He had bishoprics or diocese
all over the Middle East

00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:46.810 align:middle line:84%
and all over parts of Southern
Europe, and his church--

00:07:46.810 --> 00:07:49.390 align:middle line:84%
the number of churches he
had, the number of bishops--

00:07:49.390 --> 00:07:54.360 align:middle line:84%
was larger much, much larger
than the Church of Peter

00:07:54.360 --> 00:07:59.800 align:middle line:84%
in Rome around 100 AD, and he
was a major, major influence.

00:07:59.800 --> 00:08:02.660 align:middle line:84%
For example, for
one thing, Marcion

00:08:02.660 --> 00:08:07.340 align:middle line:84%
invented the whole system of
having dioceses and bishoprics

00:08:07.340 --> 00:08:09.600 align:middle line:84%
in the church
itself, and he also

00:08:09.600 --> 00:08:13.240 align:middle line:84%
wrote the first New
Testament canon.

00:08:13.240 --> 00:08:15.150 align:middle line:84%
He actually is the
person who came up

00:08:15.150 --> 00:08:19.060 align:middle line:84%
with the idea of bringing
the scriptures into a canon,

00:08:19.060 --> 00:08:22.000 align:middle line:84%
and then later on, once
he was excommunicated,

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.370 align:middle line:84%
then the Roman church took
over the whole process

00:08:24.370 --> 00:08:25.840 align:middle line:84%
of putting the
scriptures together.

00:08:25.840 --> 00:08:27.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they
completely obscured his name.

00:08:27.800 --> 00:08:28.883 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: That's right.

00:08:28.883 --> 00:08:30.260 align:middle line:84%
Well, not only
obscured his name,

00:08:30.260 --> 00:08:32.030 align:middle line:84%
this is a major
historical figure,

00:08:32.030 --> 00:08:34.559 align:middle line:84%
and if you use your computer,
he always comes up in red.

00:08:34.559 --> 00:08:36.109 align:middle line:84%
He even is one of
