00:08:36.109 --> 00:08:38.400 align:middle line:84%
how when you try to use sexual
terms with your computer

00:08:38.400 --> 00:08:40.000 align:middle line:84%
and it's red because
it's not allowed?

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:40.099 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:08:40.099 --> 00:08:41.299 align:middle line:90%
He comes up in red?

00:08:41.299 --> 00:08:41.340 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:08:41.340 --> 00:08:42.298 align:middle line:90%
Marcion is not allowed.

00:08:42.298 --> 00:08:43.919 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: M-A-R-C-I-O-N,
by the way.

00:08:43.919 --> 00:08:44.710 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Right.

00:08:44.710 --> 00:08:45.600 align:middle line:90%
Marcion of Pontus.

00:08:45.600 --> 00:08:46.100 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:08:46.100 --> 00:08:50.750 align:middle line:84%
So Marcion of Pontus had the
biggest early church system,

00:08:50.750 --> 00:08:53.310 align:middle line:84%
and he was the one who
put the canon together,

00:08:53.310 --> 00:08:55.260 align:middle line:90%
and then he was excommunicated.

00:08:55.260 --> 00:08:57.180 align:middle line:84%
Now, what does
excommunication mean?

00:08:57.180 --> 00:09:00.930 align:middle line:84%
It means, that he was taken
out of the line of succession

00:09:00.930 --> 00:09:02.160 align:middle line:90%
of the bishops.

00:09:02.160 --> 00:09:04.460 align:middle line:84%
And then this means that
all of the people who

00:09:04.460 --> 00:09:07.220 align:middle line:84%
were Marcionite bishops,
which was hundreds

00:09:07.220 --> 00:09:09.800 align:middle line:84%
at the time, their
powers of succession

00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:12.310 align:middle line:84%
were taken away, which
means that they then

00:09:12.310 --> 00:09:15.960 align:middle line:84%
had no direct linkage
to Christ or to Jesus.

00:09:15.960 --> 00:09:17.420 align:middle line:90%
Now, this is really fascinating.

00:09:17.420 --> 00:09:18.890 align:middle line:84%
Isn't it amazing you
haven't heard of him?

00:09:18.890 --> 00:09:18.998 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is.

00:09:18.998 --> 00:09:19.270 align:middle line:90%
I've never heard of him.

00:09:19.270 --> 00:09:21.860 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: I've talked
to lots of people, even

00:09:21.860 --> 00:09:24.565 align:middle line:84%
priests who haven't
heard of this person.

00:09:24.565 --> 00:09:26.330 align:middle line:90%
It's just absolutely incredible.

00:09:26.330 --> 00:09:30.670 align:middle line:84%
And so the reason the book
came for me was 30 years ago

00:09:30.670 --> 00:09:33.300 align:middle line:84%
after I finished getting
a master's in theology

00:09:33.300 --> 00:09:37.020 align:middle line:84%
with Matthew Fox, I wanted
to get a Ph.D. in patristics,

00:09:37.020 --> 00:09:39.390 align:middle line:84%
and I wanted to
base it on Marcion.

00:09:39.390 --> 00:09:41.190 align:middle line:90%
So here we are 30 years later--

00:09:41.190 --> 00:09:41.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You have
this character.

00:09:41.710 --> 00:09:42.460 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:09:42.460 --> 00:09:44.470 align:middle line:84%
My character and
her name is Sarah.

00:09:44.470 --> 00:09:47.880 align:middle line:84%
And Sarah is very much me in
the book in terms of her work,

00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:50.020 align:middle line:84%
and Sarah is
working on this PhD.

00:09:50.020 --> 00:09:52.470 align:middle line:84%
And this is what's of
critical importance:

00:09:52.470 --> 00:09:57.310 align:middle line:84%
Marcion believed that the early
Christian church should not

00:09:57.310 --> 00:09:59.040 align:middle line:84%
attach itself to the
Hebrew scriptures.

00:09:59.040 --> 00:10:01.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which is called
the Old Testament otherwise.

00:10:01.290 --> 00:10:05.640 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: Now,
the Christians--

00:10:05.640 --> 00:10:09.570 align:middle line:84%
what I want to call it?-- took
pieces of the Hebrew scriptures

00:10:09.570 --> 00:10:11.106 align:middle line:90%
and called it the Old Testament.

00:10:11.106 --> 00:10:13.480 align:middle line:84%
And there's lots of Hebrew
scripture they didn't include.

00:10:13.480 --> 00:10:16.630 align:middle line:84%
They just took the stuff
that backs up Christianity.

00:10:16.630 --> 00:10:22.510 align:middle line:84%
And then they attached the
Acts and the books of the Bible

00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:24.210 align:middle line:90%
to the Hebrew scriptures.

00:10:24.210 --> 00:10:27.435 align:middle line:84%
So if you take your Bible
out, 1,000 pages of it

00:10:27.435 --> 00:10:30.470 align:middle line:84%
are Hebrew scriptures now
called the Old Testament

00:10:30.470 --> 00:10:33.980 align:middle line:84%
and 200 pages of it are the
early Christian scriptures.

00:10:33.980 --> 00:10:35.250 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that amazing?

00:10:35.250 --> 00:10:36.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it is.

00:10:36.400 --> 00:10:38.430 align:middle line:84%
Even as a little kid, I
found that interesting.

00:10:38.430 --> 00:10:40.409 align:middle line:84%
I didn't understand
the need for that.

00:10:40.409 --> 00:10:41.200 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Right.

00:10:41.200 --> 00:10:44.420 align:middle line:84%
So Marcion believed-- this
is the critical thing--

00:10:44.420 --> 00:10:46.360 align:middle line:84%
that the Jewish
God-- now, there's

00:10:46.360 --> 00:10:49.550 align:middle line:84%
nothing anti-Semitic or
pejorative in Marcion's

00:10:49.550 --> 00:10:50.520 align:middle line:90%
attitude at all.

00:10:50.520 --> 00:10:53.810 align:middle line:84%
Some of the Gnostics are pretty
anti-Semitic, not Marcion.

00:10:53.810 --> 00:10:58.270 align:middle line:84%
Marcion believed that Yahweh
or Jehovah was the God of law,

00:10:58.270 --> 00:11:01.560 align:middle line:84%
and the God of creating
like human structure

00:11:01.560 --> 00:11:04.242 align:middle line:90%
and the God of human rulership.

00:11:04.242 --> 00:11:05.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Almost
kind of Saturnian.

00:11:05.700 --> 00:11:06.658 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Well, yes.

00:11:06.658 --> 00:11:09.610 align:middle line:84%
Saturnian and also the period
of time we're talking about

00:11:09.610 --> 00:11:12.970 align:middle line:84%
is like 2000 BC up
to 0 AD in terms

00:11:12.970 --> 00:11:15.800 align:middle line:84%
of the development of
the Hebrew scriptures,

00:11:15.800 --> 00:11:17.444 align:middle line:90%
and this is the Age of Aries.

00:11:17.444 --> 00:11:19.110 align:middle line:84%
The other thing we
have to throw in here

00:11:19.110 --> 00:11:20.690 align:middle line:84%
is the issue of precession
of the equinoxes.

00:11:20.690 --> 00:11:21.273 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:11:21.273 --> 00:11:26.030 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: So the Age of
Aries is 2200 BC to like 0 AD.

00:11:26.030 --> 00:11:30.287 align:middle line:84%
And then the Age of Pisces is
like 0 AD up to about 2100 AD.

00:11:30.287 --> 00:11:30.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Now.

00:11:30.870 --> 00:11:30.990 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:11:30.990 --> 00:11:31.820 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:11:31.820 --> 00:11:35.930 align:middle line:84%
So now that we're shifting
into the Age of Aquarius,

00:11:35.930 --> 00:11:37.930 align:middle line:84%
and people may wonder
what does it go backwards?

00:11:37.930 --> 00:11:39.590 align:middle line:90%
Well, precession works that way.

00:11:39.590 --> 00:11:43.670 align:middle line:84%
It goes towards Taurus,
Aries, Pisces, Aquarius.

00:11:43.670 --> 00:11:45.920 align:middle line:84%
So now that we're going
to the Age of Aquarius,

00:11:45.920 --> 00:11:48.430 align:middle line:84%
and I'm an Aquarian,
I really believe

00:11:48.430 --> 00:11:51.600 align:middle line:84%
that we need to
reevaluate, and I also

00:11:51.600 --> 00:11:53.140 align:middle line:84%
consider myself
to be a Christian.

00:11:53.140 --> 00:11:54.560 align:middle line:84%
I can't handle
being in the church

00:11:54.560 --> 00:11:55.684 align:middle line:90%
because of what's going on.

00:11:55.684 --> 00:11:58.740 align:middle line:84%
I am a Catholic, but
I've left the church.

00:11:58.740 --> 00:12:01.260 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You're doing the
journey, this young woman--

00:12:01.260 --> 00:12:02.010 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:12:02.010 --> 00:12:03.212 align:middle line:90%
In the novel, she goes--

00:12:03.212 --> 00:12:03.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That is your journey.

00:12:03.380 --> 00:12:05.130 align:middle line:84%
>>HAND CLOW: --through
her journey and she

00:12:05.130 --> 00:12:06.310 align:middle line:90%
leaves the church.

00:12:06.310 --> 00:12:08.280 align:middle line:84%
And not a lot of it's
autobiographical really,

00:12:08.280 --> 00:12:09.820 align:middle line:90%
but the process is.

00:12:09.820 --> 00:12:13.100 align:middle line:84%
So I think and she
thinks that now

00:12:13.100 --> 00:12:16.160 align:middle line:84%
that we've come into going
into the Age of Aquarius, which

00:12:16.160 --> 00:12:18.330 align:middle line:84%
is going to be much more
of an Age of Enlightenment.

00:12:18.330 --> 00:12:21.800 align:middle line:84%
The Age of Pisces has been an
age of emotional processing

00:12:21.800 --> 00:12:26.070 align:middle line:84%
because of the nature of Pisces
as a water sign and the nature

00:12:26.070 --> 00:12:28.510 align:middle line:90%
of Neptune and spirituality.

00:12:28.510 --> 00:12:33.270 align:middle line:84%
And so Marcion believed that
the God that Jesus was talking

00:12:33.270 --> 00:12:36.780 align:middle line:84%
about was a God of love
and a God of compassion.

00:12:36.780 --> 00:12:40.440 align:middle line:84%
And he simply was saying
Jesus came to this planet

00:12:40.440 --> 00:12:43.230 align:middle line:84%
and he's a very, very
high being, by the way.

00:12:43.230 --> 00:12:46.060 align:middle line:84%
This is the first
book in a trilogy,

00:12:46.060 --> 00:12:48.730 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to be exploring
who Jesus is much more

00:12:48.730 --> 00:12:50.610 align:middle line:84%
deeply in the second
and the third book,

00:12:50.610 --> 00:12:53.390 align:middle line:84%
but I wanted to set up a
foundation in the first book

00:12:53.390 --> 00:12:55.560 align:middle line:84%
because I believe
that Jesus is a very

00:12:55.560 --> 00:12:58.230 align:middle line:84%
highly, multi-dimensional
being who's actually

00:12:58.230 --> 00:13:01.810 align:middle line:84%
an integrator of the
whole universe itself.

00:13:01.810 --> 00:13:05.300 align:middle line:84%
So he came down and had an
incarnation on this planet

00:13:05.300 --> 00:13:08.530 align:middle line:84%
in order to help people
let go of the God of law,

00:13:08.530 --> 00:13:11.420 align:middle line:84%
and the need for control,
and the need for everything

00:13:11.420 --> 00:13:13.870 align:middle line:84%
to have to be specifically
a certain way,

00:13:13.870 --> 00:13:17.730 align:middle line:84%
and to bring in a
God, his father,

00:13:17.730 --> 00:13:19.970 align:middle line:90%
a God of love and compassion.

00:13:19.970 --> 00:13:24.170 align:middle line:84%
So Marcion had a whole teaching
program, and he went to Rome.

00:13:24.170 --> 00:13:26.130 align:middle line:84%
He went to Rome,
finally, in 140 AD

00:13:26.130 --> 00:13:29.310 align:middle line:84%
because he was so frustrated
by what was going on

00:13:29.310 --> 00:13:31.850 align:middle line:84%
and to plead his
case that we must not

00:13:31.850 --> 00:13:35.320 align:middle line:84%
attach the Christian scriptures
to the Hebrew scriptures.

00:13:35.320 --> 00:13:37.052 align:middle line:84%
And the novel even
explores the fact

00:13:37.052 --> 00:13:38.760 align:middle line:84%
that the Jews didn't
really appreciate it

00:13:38.760 --> 00:13:40.310 align:middle line:84%
very much, because
the Christians--

00:13:40.310 --> 00:13:41.132 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: They felt co-opted.

00:13:41.132 --> 00:13:41.510 align:middle line:90%
>>HAND CLOW: Yeah.

00:13:41.510 --> 00:13:44.093 align:middle line:84%
They picked and chose what they
liked, and then they said, oh,

00:13:44.093 --> 00:13:47.410 align:middle line:84%
and Isaiah said blah,
blah, blah back in 700 BC,

00:13:47.410 --> 00:13:49.090 align:middle line:84%
he was talking
about Jesus coming.

00:13:49.090 --> 00:13:52.260 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you're a group
of spiritual beings,

00:13:52.260 --> 00:13:54.430 align:middle line:84%
a group of Jewish
people and you don't

00:13:54.430 --> 00:13:56.325 align:middle line:84%
believe that Christ
is the messiah, what

00:13:56.325 --> 00:13:58.450 align:middle line:84%
